courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students will be able to:
(1) use basic expressions for simple daily communication;
(2) achieve a brief understanding of selected topics related to the Korean society and culture;
(3) apply independent learning strategy with emphasis on autonomous learning

By the end of the course, students will be able to:

(1) Have a basic understanding of Korean history, customs and language;
(2) Understand the underlying cultural and religious roots of Korean people’s behavior;
(3) Gain understanding about Korean economy, politics, fine arts and pop culture;
(4) To be able to analyze Korean issues and phenomenon from a cross-cultural perspective.

Upon successful completion of the course, students should be able to
(1) improve their communication skills with argumentative strategies;
(2) obtain a better listening skill by learning various types of spoken expressions used in modern Korean society;
(3) increase comprehensive understanding in written text without knowing every word inside of it;
(4) be more accustomed to traditional and modern culture in Korean.

Upon the completion of this course, students should demonstrate the ability to

 use the four language skills listening, speaking, reading and writing with confidence in a wide range of situational contexts;
 collect information independently and present in class using the appropriate language registers;
 discuss, compare and evaluate issues related to Korean society and international affairs.

Upon completion of this course, students will be able to:
(1) produce the sound of each vowel and consonant accurately;
(2) identify phonetic rules and apply them to pronunciation properly;
(3) reduce pronunciation errors;
(4) produce rhythmically correct sentences;
(5) identify meaning-change through intonation;
(6) speak accurately and fluently;
(7) ultimately increase self-confidence in speaking.

Upon the completion of this course, students should demonstrate the ability to

 expand their understanding and the use of formulaic expressions used in everyday siutation;
 understand better about sentence structure and patterns with expanded vocabulary and expressions;
 get familiar with handling of tenses and know how to change verbs into polite form;
 have some basic knowledge of Korean culture.

Upon the completion of this course, students should demonstrate the ability to

 Broaden the four language skills;
 Express detailed personal opinion using more complex sentence structure with a variety of vocabulary in both the spoken and the written language;
 Discuss, compare and evaluate issues related to Korean society and global issues.

After taking this course, students will be able to:
- improve their general reading skills and strategies;
- respond to unknown vocabularies with context clues;
- effectively grasp and comprehend the information in various Korean texts;
- enrich their knowledge of vocabularies and expressions of Korean;
- gain self-confidence to communicate in Korean;
- gain a better understanding in Korean culture, society, customs and values.
